    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72b6ddde_205a6bf2",
        "filename": "third_party/gif/SkGifImageReader.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 295,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-11T19:42:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the Chromium version\u0027s review, pkasting@ pointed out that this is different behavior from the old code, though perhaps only on mal-formed GIFs, and suggested that you \"creat[e] such a mal-formed GIF manually, deciding explicitly how to best decode it (might require testing other image viewers?), and then updating to match.\" Can you add a test image that demonstrates this?\n\n[1] https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/1122135/1/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/image-decoders/gif/gif_image_reader.cc#298",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 294,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 295,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0d16e4ad1f10f9163139b211038135a1d74b0bd2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e610535a_78e2a177",
        "filename": "third_party/gif/SkGifImageReader.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 295,
      "author": {
        "id": 8590
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-21T12:39:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "after reaching max allowed code : 4095 avail is incremented to 4096 (while adding new entry): line 309, which is more than maximum code allowed. In a correct image you will always get clear code after that which will change the avail value back to \"avail \u003d clearCode + 2;\". Also it is not possible to have a code in stream having value 4096 instead of clear code because of the maximum code size allowed in GIF : 12 bits.even if the code is 13 bit we wont be decoding it because codesize is increased only when avail \u003c SK_MAX_DICTIONARY_ENTRIES.",
      "parentUuid": "72b6ddde_205a6bf2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 294,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 295,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0d16e4ad1f10f9163139b211038135a1d74b0bd2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ac786b71_340ea1f9",
        "filename": "third_party/gif/SkGifImageReader.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 295,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-21T15:00:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You also mentioned in the chromium review that a correct image should not reach this case. But that\u0027s not the concern here. This decoder is designed to be rather lenient, due to the fact that historically, there have been encoders which created images that do not conform to the spec. Here you\u0027ve made a behavior change for malformed images, and we want to make sure that behavior change is okay.",
      "parentUuid": "e610535a_78e2a177",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 294,
        "startChar": 13,
        "endLine": 295,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "0d16e4ad1f10f9163139b211038135a1d74b0bd2",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
